00:03:57.146 --> 00:03:59.396
- Hang on. Hang on.
- Hey, let go of me, man.

00:04:01.438 --> 00:04:02.771
I can't believe I was right.

00:04:03.438 --> 00:04:05.813
Keep your mouth shut.
I'll mess you up, old man.

00:04:05.896 --> 00:04:07.355
Old man. Oh, my God.

00:04:07.438 --> 00:04:08.521
First of all,

00:04:08.980 --> 00:04:11.980
I should throw you in jail
just for calling me "old man,"

00:04:12.063 --> 00:04:14.063
but you bring that stuff back,

00:04:14.146 --> 00:04:17.355
I'll let you go 'cause I'm late
for dinner and I'm hungry as shit.

00:04:17.646 --> 00:04:18.646
Go ahead.

00:04:21.480 --> 00:04:23.646
- Tylenol PM? Am I right?
- No.

00:04:23.730 --> 00:04:26.581
It's not good for that.
It depends on what time of year you go.

00:04:26.605 --> 00:04:28.405
That makes sense.
Can I get another?

00:04:28.646 --> 00:04:30.105
We're gonna have another one?

00:04:30.188 --> 00:04:33.813
I'm just saying, we're paying today.
Maybe you can take it easy a little bit.

00:04:33.896 --> 00:04:36.396
Hey, hey. Nick. Nick.
What... What's wrong with you?

00:04:36.480 --> 00:04:39.146
Sorry. Should I not order
another drink, Detective?

00:04:39.771 --> 00:04:41.105
No. Holly, order another drink.

00:04:41.188 --> 00:04:43.480
Order as much as you want.
I was joking around.

00:04:43.563 --> 00:04:44.831
- That's not funny.
- The reason...

00:04:44.855 --> 00:04:47.605
I'm just in a great mood
because I had a great day today.

00:04:47.688 --> 00:04:50.539
- Did we have a great day or what?
- It was a fabulous day. Incredible day.

00:04:50.563 --> 00:04:52.730
Really? Did you get another hot case?

00:04:53.105 --> 00:04:53.938
Of what?

00:04:54.021 --> 00:04:55.646
"What."

00:04:55.730 --> 00:04:57.146
That was good. No, listen.

00:04:57.230 --> 00:04:58.813
Going great, kid. I promise you.

00:04:58.896 --> 00:05:01.271
It's like, uh, they're trusting me
more and more,

00:05:01.355 --> 00:05:03.563
and I, um, I wish I could tell you
what it was,

00:05:03.646 --> 00:05:04.896
but it's... it's confidential.

00:05:04.980 --> 00:05:06.771
- Wait a second.
- What?

00:05:06.855 --> 00:05:07.980
Oh, my God.

00:05:08.063 --> 00:05:09.938
- What is this?
- What is that?

00:05:10.021 --> 00:05:12.771
My baby Jimmy got it for me
for my birthday.

00:05:12.855 --> 00:05:13.688
- Jimmy!
- What?

00:05:13.771 --> 00:05:16.480
- Celebration diamonds.
- Oh, my gosh.

00:05:16.563 --> 00:05:18.188
- It's gorgeous!
- Thank you, Audrey.

00:05:18.271 --> 00:05:19.831
- Very expensive.
- Wow, Jimmy.

00:05:20.271 --> 00:05:23.230
I got you something special.
I promise, you're gonna be very happy.

00:05:23.313 --> 00:05:24.605
- Really?
- I can't wait.

00:05:24.688 --> 00:05:28.021
See, I would've pegged you, Nick,
as an Amazon gift card kinda guy,

00:05:28.105 --> 00:05:29.980
but... I'm no detective.

00:05:31.313 --> 00:05:33.105
Hey! You know what, guys?

00:05:33.188 --> 00:05:36.896
Let's toast to my friends,
Nick and Audrey.

00:05:36.980 --> 00:05:38.313
Fifteen wonderful years.

00:05:38.396 --> 00:05:39.396
Absolutely.

00:05:39.480 --> 00:05:41.688
- Fifteen.
- Here's to true love, guys.

00:05:41.771 --> 00:05:42.605
Fifteen.

00:05:42.688 --> 00:05:43.688
- True love.
- Yeah.

00:05:50.355 --> 00:05:53.980
Dinner was insane, but that's expected.

00:05:55.438 --> 00:05:56.521
But I'll tell you what,

00:05:56.605 --> 00:05:59.230
I want to record Holly
chewing her ice cubes,

00:05:59.313 --> 00:06:01.771
