00:06:19.813 --> 00:06:22.396
And I'm not sleeping with
the fan on tonight. I hate that sound.

00:06:22.813 --> 00:06:25.313
No fan necessary.
We'll crank the AC, babe.

00:06:29.813 --> 00:06:31.230
Uh-oh. What, what, what?

00:06:31.313 --> 00:06:33.233
You're gonna yell at me?
I can see this. Hang on.

00:06:33.271 --> 00:06:35.063
Why don't you do some more angry flossing?

00:06:35.896 --> 00:06:38.230
How come we haven't gone to Europe, Nick?

00:06:39.146 --> 00:06:40.480
You have to explain this to me.

00:06:41.271 --> 00:06:42.355
We never go anywhere.

00:06:42.438 --> 00:06:45.271
We travel.
I took you to the Poconos that time.

00:06:45.355 --> 00:06:46.605
What? The Poco... That was...

00:06:46.688 --> 00:06:48.105
That was for a funeral, Nick.

00:06:48.521 --> 00:06:50.980
How about, uh, when we went to Virginia

00:06:51.063 --> 00:06:53.313
when my uncle was in a hospice
and we got to see him die?

00:06:53.396 --> 00:06:54.980
- We did that.
- Ugh, Nick. Come on.

00:06:55.063 --> 00:06:56.521
I'm talking about the postcard.

00:06:56.605 --> 00:06:59.688
- You don't remember that?
- I remember it. Of course I remember it.

00:07:00.188 --> 00:07:03.271
It's been 15 years, Nick.
I don't know what we're waitin' for.

00:07:06.313 --> 00:07:08.896
Now you've gone and done it, Audrey.

00:07:08.980 --> 00:07:10.646
What? What'd I do?

00:07:12.355 --> 00:07:14.355
I told you I had something big
for you at dinner,

00:07:14.438 --> 00:07:16.605
and you couldn't wait till
tomorrow morning?

00:07:17.938 --> 00:07:18.938
No.

00:07:20.146 --> 00:07:22.355
We're finally going to Europe.
Happy anniversary.

00:07:22.938 --> 00:07:25.438
Oh, my God. I have chills.

00:07:25.521 --> 00:07:28.355
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

00:07:28.438 --> 00:07:30.480
Oh, my God! I'm so...

00:07:30.980 --> 00:07:33.480
- I ruined your surprise!
- Shh. You didn't ruin anything.

00:07:33.563 --> 00:07:35.605
You're the greatest. You deserve it.
I love you.

00:07:35.688 --> 00:07:38.230
- I love you!
- It's still a surprise. I swear.

00:07:42.396 --> 00:07:45.271
- We can afford it, right? This is all...
- We can afford it, of course.

00:07:45.355 --> 00:07:46.914
- Okay.
- I'm getting my raise this year.

00:07:46.938 --> 00:07:48.605
- Right.
- We're all set. Come on.

00:07:49.021 --> 00:07:50.396
- Hello. Hi.
- Hello.

00:07:50.480 --> 00:07:52.271
So, uh, we are on our honeymoon,

00:07:52.355 --> 00:07:54.896
and I was wondering
if we could possibly get an upgrade

00:07:54.980 --> 00:07:57.355
because I have miles. Maybe...

00:07:57.438 --> 00:08:00.730
I don't even know if it's from
this airline, but do they expire, or...

00:08:00.813 --> 00:08:02.980
Sir, you would have needed
to request that in advance.

00:08:03.063 --> 00:08:04.703
- Yeah.
- Right this way, please.

00:08:04.730 --> 00:08:07.313
- Thank you. I'm so sorry.
- We did try advance. I tried calling.

00:08:07.396 --> 00:08:09.271
- And, um, nobody...
- Who'd you call?

00:08:09.355 --> 00:08:10.896
- Crazy busy signals.
- Really?

00:08:10.980 --> 00:08:12.980
- It's the busy signals!
- Who did you try to call?

00:08:17.188 --> 00:08:19.355
I don't want to give it away.
It was the butler.

00:08:19.438 --> 00:08:20.813
The butler did it.

00:08:21.605 --> 00:08:23.271
It's never the butler who did it.

00:08:24.230 --> 00:08:26.021
I don't even think there are butlers.

00:08:26.105 --> 00:08:29.271
That's just a word created
for those goofy books you're addicted to.

00:08:29.355 --> 00:08:31.313
Would you just please, please shh?

00:08:31.396 --> 00:08:34.438
Leave my books alone, okay?
Just let me read.

00:08:34.521 --> 00:08:36.563
I just like... Makes me happy.

00:08:36.646 --> 00:08:38.521
Are you okay? You're cranky.
Are you bored?

00:08:38.605 --> 00:08:40.396
- I'm gonna go to sleep.
- Take a nap.

00:08:40.938 --> 00:08:42.578
- Are you okay with that?
- Wait, don't...

00:08:42.646 --> 00:08:45.313
But just, please, don't...
don't lay all the way back.

00:08:45.896 --> 00:08:47.313
- Don't take it back?
- No.

00:08:47.396 --> 00:08:49.146
Why? You don't want
my double chin to show?

00:08:49.230 --> 00:08:51.896
It's not your chins, okay. It's just rude.

00:08:51.980 --> 00:08:52.855
Yes.

00:08:52.938 --> 00:08:54.578
- Okay. 'Cause you splay out.
- All right.

00:08:54.646 --> 00:08:57.771
And then your seat is in, like,
the lap of the guy behind you.

00:08:57.855 --> 00:09:00.771
- So just be considerate of everybody.
- I'll stay up. Thank you.

00:09:01.605 --> 00:09:02.646
Timber.

00:09:11.355 --> 00:09:12.813
Oh, excuse me.

00:09:12.896 --> 00:09:14.313
- Hi.
- Hello. Hi.

