Jesus.

00:10:25.313 --> 00:10:26.563
Yes. I...

00:10:27.146 --> 00:10:28.938
Yep. I know, right?

00:10:29.021 --> 00:10:31.146
I just cannot sleep on these things.

00:10:31.396 --> 00:10:33.021
So what brings you across the pond?

00:10:33.105 --> 00:10:36.063
Actually, it's my... it's my honeymoon.

00:10:36.146 --> 00:10:37.646
Oh. Congratulations.

00:10:37.730 --> 00:10:39.521
- Thank you.
- Where's your husband?

00:10:40.105 --> 00:10:41.105
Dead.

00:10:41.521 --> 00:10:44.063
Asleep. He's dead... dead asleep.

00:10:44.146 --> 00:10:46.188
We've actually been married for 15 years,

00:10:46.271 --> 00:10:49.688
but we just have been very, very,
very, very busy.

00:10:49.938 --> 00:10:53.188
Then a toast to the whirlwind
that is your life.

00:10:54.396 --> 00:10:55.438
Yes.

00:10:55.521 --> 00:10:56.688
- Sorry, ma'am.
- Oh, yes!

00:10:56.771 --> 00:10:58.730
The bar is for
first class passengers only.

00:10:58.813 --> 00:11:01.230
Of course. Of course it is.
I'm so sorry, yes.

00:11:01.313 --> 00:11:04.480
I will head back to the lower class cabin

00:11:04.563 --> 00:11:06.771
and sit where I should and, uh...

00:11:07.313 --> 00:11:08.313
shovel some coal.

00:11:08.355 --> 00:11:09.480
She's my guest.

00:11:09.563 --> 00:11:12.230
