01:04:43.938 --> 01:04:44.980
She was right there.

01:04:45.563 --> 01:04:48.105
You should have never come to Lake Como.

01:04:48.396 --> 01:04:50.480
- Wait a minute.
- We know about you and Cavendish.

01:04:50.563 --> 01:04:53.063
- You know nothing.
- We know you're still in love,

01:04:53.146 --> 01:04:55.230
and we know that love is tough
without money.

01:04:55.313 --> 01:04:56.313
Isn't it, Suzi?

01:04:56.438 --> 01:04:58.730
I'll take your word for it.
You're the one whose shoes

01:04:58.813 --> 01:05:00.453
still got a sticker from Marshalls on it.

01:05:00.480 --> 01:05:02.560
- They have name brands now!
- How dare you?

01:05:02.605 --> 01:05:04.247
- They have name brands now!
- How dare you?

01:05:04.271 --> 01:05:06.063
- What?
- These are from Target.

01:05:06.146 --> 01:05:08.480
- How could you not tell me?
- I don't look at your...

01:05:08.563 --> 01:05:10.021
Shut up!

01:05:10.105 --> 01:05:12.605
- Oh!
- Suzi, don't. Please, don't do this.

01:05:12.688 --> 01:05:15.248
No matter what you do,
you're not gonna be safe. I'm telling you.

01:05:15.313 --> 01:05:17.605
One murderer always double-crosses
the other murderer.

01:05:17.688 --> 01:05:20.230
- She reads the books.
- It's just a cliché of the genre!

01:05:20.313 --> 01:05:21.646
I'm telling you!

01:05:24.230 --> 01:05:25.813
Hey! Halloween!

01:05:27.521 --> 01:05:29.021
No, no, no! Oh, my God!

01:05:29.105 --> 01:05:30.105
Go, go, go!

01:05:30.355 --> 01:05:32.480
Cavendish, you move,
I'll blow your head off!

01:05:35.646 --> 01:05:36.813
Shoot <i>at </i>him!

01:05:40.855 --> 01:05:42.813
Oh, babe, you're the worst shot!

01:05:43.063 --> 01:05:45.438
Those were warning shots, honey!

01:05:45.521 --> 01:05:47.646
- Oh, yes! I go fast!
- Go!

01:05:48.730 --> 01:05:51.230
Ambulance! <i>Emergencia!</i>

01:05:54.271 --> 01:05:55.271
Oh!

01:06:00.563 --> 01:06:02.730
Okay, Suzi.
You've gotta tell me who did this.

01:06:02.813 --> 01:06:04.271
Slow down. Don't use your words.

01:06:04.355 --> 01:06:06.480
Let's charade it, okay.
Just tell me with your hand.

01:06:06.938 --> 01:06:08.813
Uh, claw. Bear claw.

01:06:08.896 --> 01:06:10.230
No. Grizzly bear claw.

01:06:10.313 --> 01:06:12.021
Oh! Chewy. Chewy.

01:06:12.105 --> 01:06:13.813
So it's Sergei? No, Sergei's dead.

01:06:14.313 --> 01:06:15.396
Hey!

01:06:16.480 --> 01:06:19.396
Have you got tires on your feet? Good God!

01:06:20.230 --> 01:06:22.188
Spooning. Eating. Uh...

01:06:22.271 --> 01:06:24.188
Ice cream. No, no. Gelato. Gelato?

01:06:24.271 --> 01:06:27.230
Oh, God. It's amazing how pretty
you are when you're... I'm sorry.

01:06:27.480 --> 01:06:28.313
Hey.

01:06:28.396 --> 01:06:29.855
Hey! Come on!

01:06:32.271 --> 01:06:33.605
Oh, shoot!

01:06:45.813 --> 01:06:46.730
Hey!

01:06:50.188 --> 01:06:51.855
Ba-ba-ba-ba!

01:06:52.230 --> 01:06:54.355
Crazy... crazy... Crazy mad love!

01:06:54.605 --> 01:06:56.813
It's crazy 'cause you're madly in love
with Cavendish.

01:06:57.355 --> 01:06:59.355
It's Cavendish, no?
<i>Sleeping With the Ene...</i>

01:06:59.438 --> 01:07:00.480
Sleeping.

01:07:00.563 --> 01:07:01.688
You're not sleeping.

01:07:01.980 --> 01:07:04.563
- She's dead now?
- I don't know why this keeps happening!

01:07:04.646 --> 01:07:06.438
<i>Let's go!
We gotta get out of here.</i>

01:07:06.521 --> 01:07:08.361
- <i>Oh, my God. Come on.
- Where?</i>

01:07:09.188 --> 01:07:11.521
Close the airports! Search house to house!

01:07:11.605 --> 01:07:14.438
As God as my witness,
I will find Nick and Audrey Spitz.

01:07:15.188 --> 01:07:16.355
- Inspector?
- Yes?

01:07:16.438 --> 01:07:18.771
I have Nick and Audrey Spitz
on the phone for you.

01:07:18.855 --> 01:07:20.646
- Huh?
- Nick and Audrey Spitz.

01:07:22.896 --> 01:07:23.896
Where are you?

01:07:24.063 --> 01:07:26.688
We are on our way
to Quince's villa right now.

01:07:27.396 --> 01:07:29.563
Oh, okay.

01:07:29.646 --> 01:07:32.396
I'm sorry, I wasn't prepared
for you to actually answer that.

01:07:32.813 --> 01:07:34.230
We are being framed right now.

01:07:34.313 --> 01:07:37.271
You meet us at the villa,
we will reveal the killer.

01:07:38.230 --> 01:07:39.230
That kinda rhymed.

01:07:40.188 --> 01:07:41.355
Which is cool, I think.

01:07:52.230 --> 01:07:54.021
- Look at this place.
- Let's go.

01:07:54.105 --> 01:07:55.980
- Oh, my God.
- This is big.

01:07:56.063 --> 01:07:59.813
This is a big house.
This is what they call rich people shit.

01:07:59.896 --> 01:08:01.938
<i>Lord Cavendish is expecting us.</i>

01:08:02.271 --> 01:08:04.021
Second floor, eighth door on the left.

01:08:04.105 --> 01:08:05.985
Yes, that's right.
That's what he told us, yeah.

01:08:06.021 --> 01:08:09.105
Okay, so take a five-spotter.

01:08:09.188 --> 01:08:11.938
Your five euros is how much American-wise?

01:08:12.230 --> 01:08:13.355
Six American dollars.

01:08:13.438 --> 01:08:15.646
Oh, that's, uh... that's more than I...

01:08:15.730 --> 01:08:18.450
- Can I get a half a euro back...
- Oh, God. Please, Nick. Thank you.

01:08:18.521 --> 01:08:20.521
I didn't know they were ahead of us
with the money.

01:08:21.271 --> 01:08:23.396
- Second floor...
- I got no bullets left,

01:08:23.480 --> 01:08:26.146
so we'll bluff 'em
until Interpol gets here.

01:08:26.230 --> 01:08:27.910
Honey, you just gotta be careful.

01:08:27.938 --> 01:08:30.896
This guy has killed four people,
that we know of.

01:08:31.188 --> 01:08:33.271
Good news is, we know who did it.

01:08:33.355 --> 01:08:35.021
- Okay.
- Hard part is over with.

01:08:35.105 --> 01:08:35.980
Okay.

01:08:36.063 --> 01:08:37.063
And...

01:08:37.480 --> 01:08:38.605
What's up, Dish?

01:08:38.980 --> 01:08:41.355
Stay still!
I'll shoot you right in the six-pack!

01:08:41.438 --> 01:08:43.105
- You hear me, bitch?
- Calm down, babe.

01:08:43.396 --> 01:08:46.188
Make a move! I dare you!

01:08:46.271 --> 01:08:47.188
I dare...

01:08:47.271 --> 01:08:48.271
Oh, my God!

01:08:48.438 --> 01:08:49.855
- He's dead.
- He's dead.

01:08:50.188 --> 01:08:51.521
- Okay, he's dead.
- Oh, my God.

01:08:51.605 --> 01:08:54.105
- What the hell?
- Oh, God. Case reopened, babe.

01:08:54.188 --> 01:08:55.855
They must have poisoned his drink!

01:08:55.938 --> 01:08:58.021
- Nick!
- And look at his face. It's...

01:08:58.105 --> 01:09:01.480
I mean, besides the foaming mouth,
he still kinda looks good.

01:09:01.563 --> 01:09:02.646
What is with this man?

01:09:04.021 --> 01:09:06.622
We told the police. We called the police.
We told 'em to come here.

01:09:06.646 --> 01:09:08.021
- Yes.
- We've got to stop them.

01:09:08.396 --> 01:09:11.813
It's not like canceling a pizza, honey.
You tell 'em to show up, they show up.

01:09:11.896 --> 01:09:13.813
If he's not the killer, who is the killer?

01:09:13.896 --> 01:09:17.146
And if we don't know who the killer is
before they get here, we're screwed!

01:09:17.230 --> 01:09:18.313
Do you understand this?

01:09:18.396 --> 01:09:20.230
He's gotta be here in this house.

01:09:20.313 --> 01:09:23.813
This is gorgeous wallpaper.
Is that fabric? Is this embossed?

01:09:23.896 --> 01:09:27.230
Sweetheart, you're losing it!
You're making me nuts right now!

01:09:27.313 --> 01:09:28.521
No, I know. Hold on. Okay.

01:09:28.605 --> 01:09:30.230
All right, it's good.

01:09:30.313 --> 01:09:31.473
You all right? You breathing?

01:09:31.521 --> 01:09:33.480
- I have to breathe through this.
- Look at me.

01:09:34.271 --> 01:09:36.313
- We gotta turn ourselves in.
- Wait, what?

01:09:36.396 --> 01:09:38.855
They're all gonna show up.
If we run, they're gonna shoot us.

01:09:38.938 --> 01:09:40.813
What do you mean?
We're gonna just go to jail?

01:09:40.896 --> 01:09:42.771
It's better than getting shot, ain't it?

01:09:43.521 --> 01:09:45.521
I don't feel... I don't feel good.

01:09:45.605 --> 01:09:46.938
- Babe.
- Oh, God.

01:09:47.021 --> 01:09:48.313
It's an Italian prison.

01:09:48.396 --> 01:09:50.105
You know the food's gonna be incredible.

01:09:50.188 --> 01:09:52.646
We'll have meatballs
and pesto sauce and all that.

01:09:52.730 --> 01:09:54.563
It's not co-ed, honey. All right?

01:09:54.646 --> 01:09:56.605
We're... We're not gonna be
in jail together.

01:09:56.688 --> 01:09:57.688
I know.

01:09:58.021 --> 01:09:59.230
Why did you lie to me?

01:10:02.563 --> 01:10:03.563
'Cause I was...

01:10:04.063 --> 01:10:06.105
I was, uh... I was embarrassed.

01:10:06.396 --> 01:10:07.438
With me?

01:10:08.146 --> 01:10:09.605
Why? I...

01:10:10.105 --> 01:10:12.980
I could've helped you figure that out.
That's why we're together.

01:10:13.063 --> 01:10:14.063
I know.

01:10:14.188 --> 01:10:16.730
Remember when I couldn't pay
my rent at the salon,

01:10:16.813 --> 01:10:21.063
and then you were like, "Oh, okay."
You got that boot off my landlord's car.

01:10:21.355 --> 01:10:23.480
- That got me another week.
- Yeah, I remember.

01:10:23.563 --> 01:10:25.603
Remember when your cholesterol
was through the roof?

01:10:25.855 --> 01:10:28.563
And then I made you eat egg whites?
You hate egg whites.

01:10:28.646 --> 01:10:30.438
And I made you do it,
and I did it with you.

01:10:30.521 --> 01:10:33.105
You helped me not miss yolks anymore.

01:10:33.188 --> 01:10:35.331
That's right. That's what we do.
We do things together.

01:10:35.355 --> 01:10:38.730
So can we please
just figure this out, too?

01:10:38.813 --> 01:10:40.605
We just don't know who did it.

01:10:40.688 --> 01:10:42.896
But Nick, we know who didn't do it.

01:10:42.980 --> 01:10:44.271
- All right?
- Right.

01:10:44.355 --> 01:10:48.396
So let's just go downstairs
and act like we figured it out.

01:10:48.896 --> 01:10:51.813
If we're gonna do that, we gotta...
we just gotta look confident.

01:10:51.896 --> 01:10:54.730
All right. If we're gonna look confident,
we've gotta dress it.

01:10:54.813 --> 01:10:56.646
I already know what I wanna wear.

01:10:57.021 --> 01:10:58.021
What?

01:11:11.730 --> 01:11:12.980
What's up, fools?

01:11:13.063 --> 01:11:15.355
Okay, we solved the case. Boom.

01:11:15.438 --> 01:11:18.563
Yo, yo! Where'd you get the clothes?
It's a little much.

01:11:19.063 --> 01:11:19.938
Um...

01:11:20.021 --> 01:11:23.146
I found this beautiful dress
in a random closet.

01:11:23.230 --> 01:11:25.605
- You're looking gorgeous, by the way.
- Thanks, baby.

01:11:25.688 --> 01:11:28.313
- And he got this stunning tux...
- Mm-hmm.

01:11:28.688 --> 01:11:29.688
...off a...

01:11:30.230 --> 01:11:31.605
Oh, why candy-coat it?

01:11:31.688 --> 01:11:32.813
- A corpse.
- Yeah.

01:11:32.896 --> 01:11:34.188
There's another corpse?

01:11:34.271 --> 01:11:35.646
Jeez! Sorry, yes.

01:11:35.730 --> 01:11:37.396
Upstairs, eighth door on the left.

01:11:38.396 --> 01:11:40.855
To whom does this dead corpse belong?

01:11:40.938 --> 01:11:42.271
Oh, yeah. You guys don't know.

01:11:42.355 --> 01:11:43.622
- Bad news, guys.
- It's terrible.

01:11:43.646 --> 01:11:44.563
Cavendish is dead.

01:11:45.980 --> 01:11:48.563
You stole the tux off Charlie's dead body?

01:11:48.646 --> 01:11:51.164
And it fits perfectly.
Little tight in the crotch, to be honest.

01:11:51.188 --> 01:11:53.247
Just kidding. No, he's got me beat.
He's got me beat.

01:11:53.271 --> 01:11:54.938
Wait. Where's Suzi?

01:11:55.313 --> 01:11:56.688
- She's dead.
- Dead.

01:11:56.771 --> 01:11:57.771
- Oh!
- Oh, my God!

01:11:57.855 --> 01:12:00.563
Y'all are like the miniature
Manson Family!

01:12:00.646 --> 01:12:02.122
- No, no, no.
- Nick and Audrey Spitz,

01:12:02.146 --> 01:12:03.813
- you are under arrest.
- Listen.

01:12:03.896 --> 01:12:05.521
<i>Ferme la bouche.</i> Is that what it is?

01:12:05.605 --> 01:12:08.271
- Just give us a second. We got this.
- We got this. Let's go.

01:12:08.355 --> 01:12:09.355
Thank you.

01:12:10.521 --> 01:12:14.230
All right. Ladies and gentlemen,
let's review the facts.

01:12:14.313 --> 01:12:15.188
Malcolm Quince,

01:12:15.271 --> 01:12:17.146
he was the first to get murdered.

01:12:17.230 --> 01:12:18.855
We all assumed it was Tobey.

01:12:18.938 --> 01:12:21.146
- No, we all assumed you did it.
- Mm-hmm.

01:12:21.230 --> 01:12:23.855
- Okay.
- Yeah, but Tobey hated his father,

01:12:23.938 --> 01:12:26.896
and he stood to inherit
billions of dollars.

01:12:26.980 --> 01:12:29.521
- Until he caught some lead to the dome.
- Mm-hmm.

01:12:29.605 --> 01:12:31.730
- Can you feel me, Raja?
- Pew-pew-pew!

01:12:32.021 --> 01:12:33.146
- There it is.
- And then,

01:12:33.230 --> 01:12:36.355
before Sergei was shot,
he told us that the Colonel did it.

01:12:36.438 --> 01:12:37.438
He told you what?

01:12:37.521 --> 01:12:40.771
But we know you didn't do it, Colonel,
because we saw you flossing your teeth

01:12:40.855 --> 01:12:42.813
when we were shimmying
by your window that night.

01:12:43.105 --> 01:12:45.855
You two were spying on me in my bathroom?

01:12:45.938 --> 01:12:49.605
Trust me, I did... We saw a lot of shit
that night that I did not want to see.

01:12:49.688 --> 01:12:53.271
I mean, apologize ahead of time.
We had to see you guys having sex.

01:12:53.563 --> 01:12:54.646
You, um...

01:12:54.730 --> 01:12:56.480
You... saw that?

01:12:56.563 --> 01:12:58.230
Maharajah, some advice for you.

01:12:58.313 --> 01:13:00.313
Maybe grab the bottom and squeeze.

01:13:01.480 --> 01:13:02.896
Huh. Word.

01:13:03.438 --> 01:13:04.271
Anyway...

01:13:04.355 --> 01:13:05.563
French fries. Yes.

01:13:05.646 --> 01:13:08.063
Actually, Juan Carlos,
you had nothing to do with this.

01:13:08.146 --> 01:13:09.866
You couldn't have had anything
to do with it

01:13:09.938 --> 01:13:12.605
because you were with us
when Suzi got killed.

01:13:12.688 --> 01:13:14.408
- So it wasn't you.
- Mm-mm.

01:13:14.480 --> 01:13:15.855
- It wasn't you.
- Mm-mm.

01:13:15.938 --> 01:13:17.688
- It wasn't you.
- No.

01:13:17.771 --> 01:13:18.896
It wasn't you.

01:13:19.271 --> 01:13:20.813
Holy shit! Maybe we did do it.

01:13:20.896 --> 01:13:22.355
- What?
- Did you?

01:13:22.438 --> 01:13:24.398
- Because listen...
- What did you just say to me?

01:13:24.480 --> 01:13:26.730
- I'm just messing around.
- There it is.

01:13:26.813 --> 01:13:28.813
- And he's clapping.
- Going to jail. Thanks, babe.

01:13:28.855 --> 01:13:31.813
I'm glad we finally
are all on the same page.

01:13:32.105 --> 01:13:35.688
Now, since the first murder occurred
in French territorial waters,

01:13:35.771 --> 01:13:39.188
I will be taking you to Paris
to be arraigned and tried.

01:13:39.271 --> 01:13:41.414
At least we're going to Paris.
You always wanted to go.

01:13:41.438 --> 01:13:44.271
Honey, if you keep making jokes
at a time like this,

01:13:44.355 --> 01:13:45.855
it's not gonna make this go away.

01:13:45.938 --> 01:13:49.188
Lucky for you, since 1977,

01:13:49.271 --> 01:13:51.980
there has been no death penalty
under French law.

01:13:52.355 --> 01:13:53.771
French law.

01:13:53.855 --> 01:13:54.771
French law.

01:13:54.855 --> 01:13:56.355
The French law. Yeah.

01:13:56.438 --> 01:13:59.021
Surely, Inspector, you of all people

01:13:59.105 --> 01:14:01.896
are familiar
with the French inheritance law.

01:14:02.271 --> 01:14:04.230
Are you implying I have bastard children?

01:14:04.855 --> 01:14:05.771
Well, I wasn't.

01:14:05.855 --> 01:14:06.938
Because I do.

01:14:07.021 --> 01:14:08.855
I was surprised you knew about them.

01:14:09.146 --> 01:14:10.771
I love those little bastards.

01:14:11.105 --> 01:14:15.230
Okay. Anyway, um,
the French law states that a man's estate

01:14:15.313 --> 01:14:18.230
must be divided equally
amongst his children.

01:14:18.521 --> 01:14:20.855
So it wouldn't matter what the will said.

01:14:20.938 --> 01:14:22.563
Straight up, Maharajah.

01:14:22.646 --> 01:14:26.730
The kids were gonna get the money,
whether the old man married Suzi or not.

01:14:26.813 --> 01:14:29.771
Mm-hmm.
But both of Malcolm's children are dead.

01:14:30.063 --> 01:14:31.605
- Both?
- Yes. Tobey,

01:14:31.688 --> 01:14:34.813
and the son he had
with Madeleine LeBoutillier..

01:14:34.896 --> 01:14:36.813
That boy died at childbirth.

01:14:37.105 --> 01:14:38.105
Did he, Colonel?

01:14:38.521 --> 01:14:40.521
I spoke to my partner in New York City.

01:14:40.605 --> 01:14:44.063
I said, get the death certificates
for Madeleine and the son.

01:14:44.146 --> 01:14:45.980
He could only find one for Madeleine.

01:14:46.063 --> 01:14:48.539
But then I started thinking,
maybe there's no death certificate

01:14:48.563 --> 01:14:50.146
because there was no death.

01:14:50.230 --> 01:14:54.896
Nonsense. Malcolm desperately wanted a boy
to sire the next generation of Quinces.

01:14:54.980 --> 01:14:56.605
He would never abandon a son.

01:14:56.688 --> 01:14:57.688
But...

01:14:58.521 --> 01:14:59.563
what if it was a daughter?

01:14:59.646 --> 01:15:00.872
- Yes!
- What if it was a daughter?

01:15:00.896 --> 01:15:02.271
The love of his life dies,

01:15:02.355 --> 01:15:04.938
dies giving birth
to his unwanted daughter.

01:15:05.021 --> 01:15:07.605
- Yes!
- It almost makes sense.

01:15:07.688 --> 01:15:09.896
- It does! It kinda does!
- It makes total sense.

01:15:09.980 --> 01:15:11.563
He gave her away.

01:15:11.646 --> 01:15:12.771
Then where is she now?

01:15:12.855 --> 01:15:15.521
Well, she could be anywhere.
She could have got married.

01:15:15.605 --> 01:15:18.396
She could've joined a gang,
changed her name. Who knows? Carry on.

01:15:18.688 --> 01:15:20.230
- Changed her name.
- Ah!

01:15:20.313 --> 01:15:22.855
- You changed your name.
- Yes.

01:15:22.938 --> 01:15:24.646
Your real last name isn't Ballard.

01:15:24.938 --> 01:15:25.938
So?

01:15:26.146 --> 01:15:28.146
Lots of artists change their names.

01:15:28.230 --> 01:15:30.146
Lady Gaga's real name isn't Lady Gaga.

01:15:30.230 --> 01:15:32.438
Yes, Lady Gaga. "Paparazzi," yes, good.

01:15:32.521 --> 01:15:35.896
But every Grace Ballard superfan knows

